Author-Email:
Author-Name: Rodríguez Daponte, Rocío
Author-Email:
Author-Name: González Vázquez, Encarnación
Author-Email:
Keywords: Corporate social responsibility, Stakeholders theory, Cluster analysis
Title: Corporate Social Responsability and Stakeholders: A Cluster Analysis
Abstract: In the last years the business sector has come developing an increasing effort in the development of Corporate Social Responsibility activities. This behavior is sustained in the expectations of these improve the relationships with stakeholders and business reputation. This research measure the CSR using stakeholders approach and a cluster analysis is applied on a sample of galician companies. The obtained result is the identification of four segments of companies that provide different models for CSR implementation management.
